<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.97.20975.figure48>
    dc:description "Figure 48. Xylopia villosa. A Flower, lateral view B Pedicel and torus of fruit C Outer petal, adaxial view D Inner petal, adaxial view E Shoot F Torus with sepals and staminal cone attached G Close-up of portion of inflorescence. A, C-G from Bernardi 8679 (A) B from Chevalier 22516 (P)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199133" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.97.20975.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Distributions of Xylopia africana, X. globosa, and X. staudtii. Bolder lines represent country borders, fainter lines lakes and major rivers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199095" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.97.20975.figure43>
